cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.CG

The paper deals with the computational complexity of solving the Lemmings game, which involves assigning skills to a group of creatures to guide them through a hazardous landscape. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of specific skills to modify the behavior of the creatures also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The optimization problem of saving the highest number of lemmings can be seen as a game theory problem (cs.GT), and the study of the landscape and the creatures' movements can be seen as a computational geometry problem (cs.CG).
